Crestar , Grad & Walker in deal . Crestar Energy Inc said early Wednesday that it has an agreement to acquire Grad & Walker Energy Corp in a deal worth about $ 336 . 2 million . Under the deal , Crestar would acquire Grad & Walker in exchange for $ 13 . 50 cash or , at the election of depositing shareholders , 0 . 509 Crestar common shares for each Grad & Walker common share . A maximum of 5 million Crestar common shares will be available under the share election . If all Grad & Walker common shares are tendered , the value of the offer will be about $ 336 . 2 million , it said . As recently as Monday , Crestar Chief Executive Barry Jackson said the company did not have a deal for Grad & Walker . Crestar operates in areas close to Grad & Walker ' s , which include the Marengo and Mantario East oil plays in southwestern Saskatchewan and Three Hills Creek in central Alberta . Grad & Walker Resources Ltd , a holding company , and certain officers and directors of Grad & Walker , who collectively hold about 21 percent of the outstanding Grad & Walker shares on a fully diluted basis , have agreed to deposit and not withdraw their Grad & Walker shares under the offer . Crestar ' s offer has the unanimous support of the boards of directors of both companies . Grad & Walker has agreed to pay Crestar a non - completion fee of 2 . 8 percent plus costs in certain circumstances and has agreed not to solicit other transaction proposals , the companies said . - - New York Newsdesk 212 - 859 - 1610 
